CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1963, pg. 14 reads: "Mt. Nebo Nobles Invest - Nobles of Mt. Nebo Shriners Lodge 4 made another investment in civil rights, recently, when they gave a check, for the NAACP, to a board member, Matthew Moore (left center). There presentation is made by illustrious Potentate Lewis Gilbert.  Other nobles are (left to right) Samuel Wright, Lawrence Walker, William Dewitt, Willie L. Green, Clarence Atkins, Grady Estelle, John McFee, Hewlett Woods and James Brown. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Matthew Moore receiving check for NAACP from Mt. Nebo Shriners Lodge 4 member Lewis Gilbert, with other members, from left: Samuel Wright, Lawrence Walker, William Dewitt, Willie L. Green, Clarence Atkins, Grady Estelle, John McFee, Hewlett Woods, and James Brown looking on, in front of Gilbert's barbershop
